    <item>
      <title>全球衰退担心吞噬华尔街的关税报复</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-04-04/global-recession-trade-engulfs-wall-street-on-tariff-retaliation</link>
      <description><![CDATA[在金融市场的每个角落，从股票到债券再到商品，投资者都向唐纳德·特朗普传达了同样的信息：他释放的贸易战争威胁要引发全球衰退＆mdash;和快速。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-04-04/global-recession-trade-engulfs-wall-street-on-tariff-retaliation</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 04 Apr 2025 15:27:35 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>自covid以来，美国股票以S＆amp; p头的升级为最糟糕的一周</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-04-04/us-stock-futures-sink-as-china-retaliates-against-trump-tariffs</link>
      <description><![CDATA[S＆amp; P 500指数在过去的两次会议上损失了5.2万亿美元的市场价值之后，美国股票在2020年3月以来最糟糕的一周，因为美联储主席杰罗姆·鲍威尔（Jerome Powell）表示，特朗普政府的关税“可能会对通货膨胀产生持久影响”。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-04-04/us-stock-futures-sink-as-china-retaliates-against-trump-tariffs</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 04 Apr 2025 10:43:41 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
